The paper deals with geometric query problems and their efficient solutions, which falls under the scope of computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of preprocessing techniques to optimize query time suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS). The problem of finding the largest empty circle can also be viewed as a combinatorial optimization problem (cs.DM). The study of boundaries of convex and simple polygons and point sets suggests a focus on computational geometry and computational topology (cs.GR). Finally, the use of geometric query problems in practical applications such as robotics and computer vision suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
